                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d492">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">123J634/354: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-06-21T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 21, 1935—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>181. Your nomination was confirmed by Senate June 14th and President has
                    appointed you June 18th to be Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of
                    the United States to China. Letter of credence being mailed to you care of
                    Consulate General Nanking on steamer <hi rend="italic">President Grant</hi> from
                    Seattle June 22nd. Your status as Minister will continue until day you present
                    credentials Nanking. On that day you will take oath as Ambassador. Salary at
                    $17,500 per annum begins when letter of credence presented. Deficiency
                    appropriation is being requested and it is expected this will be approved by
                    time you <pb facs="0635" n="523" xml:id="pg_523"/> are ready to present
                    credentials. If deficiency appropriation delayed for any reason, further
                    instructions will be issued in due time. Your traveling expenses and usual per
                    diem on trip to Nanking should be charged to item for travel in your district as
                    already established in Legation’s regular contingent expense allotment for
                    coming fiscal year.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
